The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICL on ICC agenda
                                                   ICL on ICC agenda
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) will discuss the rebel Indian Cricket Leagues (ICL) request for recognition when they gather in Perth on Saturday and Sunday.         
	Many international players, who have aligned with the ICL and have subsequently been banned by their respective cricket boards, will keep their fingers crossed for the ICC board meeting.         
	The ICC board will gather in Perth on January 31 and February 1 for the first of the four meetings it holds in a year. The ICC board will discuss the ICLs application, said an ICC statement issued on Wednesday.         
	The ICC board will also discuss preparations for the Champions Trophy 2009. Also on the table would be the issue of the Test championship.         
	The other items on the agenda:         
	Zimbabwe; Future Tours Programme post-2012.                                                                                                                       
